-- tDer Anger neu gedacht / The Village Green Reconsidered -- tEin neuer Ort des Glaubens / A New Place of Faith -- tDer veredelte Heustadl / The Refined Barn -- tDie königlichen Berge / The Royal Mountains -- tTexte Essays -- tStrategien für ein Leben fernab der Metropolen / Strategies for Life Away from the Big Cities -- tAUTOREN / AUTHORS -- tADRESSEN / ADDRESSES -- tBILDNACHWEIS / PICTURE CREDITS -- tIMPRESSUM / IMPRINT0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDie Alternative zur Stadt ist das Leben auf dem Land. Aber was macht attraktive Orte und intakte Dorfstrukturen aus? Welche planerischen Strategien und Instrumente helfen, diese lebendig zu halten anstatt Freiflächen mit Einfamilienhaussiedlungen und Gewerbegebieten zu zersiedeln? Wie kann Architektur dazu beitragen, Identität zu schaffen beziehungsweise zu bewahren? In Bayern haben Katinka Temme und Daniel Reisch viele gute Beispiele gefunden. Sie untersuchen zusammen mit ihren Co-Autoren die Möglichkeiten von Lückenschluss, Nachverdichtung, Neuplanung, Umgestaltung, Nachnutzung – kurz architektonische Mittel zur Stärkung regionaler Identität. Das Buch liefert 20 Architekturbeispiele, die zeigen, wie eine tatsächliche Perspektive Land gelingen kann.  aThe alternative to the city is life in the countryside. Yet what constitutes attractive locations and intact village structures? Which planning strategies and instruments help to keep them alive instead of covering open spaces with sprawling single-family housing estates and business parks? How can architecture contribute to creating or maintaining identity? In Bavaria, Katinka Temme and Daniel Reisch have discovered several good examples. They investigate the possibilities of closing the gaps, redensification, replanning, redesigning, reuse - in short the architectural means of strengthening regional identity. In addition to entertaining theoretical discussions, the book presents 20 good examples of architecture that show how an actual rural perspective can succeed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 7aARCHITECTURE / Methods & Materials.2bisacsh1 aAmann, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBembé Dellinger, Beer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDilcher, Vinzenz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEmge, Rico, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFassl, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFischer, Almannai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaimerl, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNagel, Reiner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNagler, Florian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeuberger, Günther, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPawson, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReisch, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReisch, Daniel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTemme, Katinka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTemme, Katinka, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZitzelsberger, Max Otto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2020z9783110704679oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG0 cprintz9783955